File: Communications Minister Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams. JOHANNESBURG - Communications Minister Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams has voluntarily submitted herself to appear before the ANC Integrity Commission. This comes after media reports of dodgy business dealings by officials in state-owned entities under her portfolio, including members of her family. Lockdown: Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams apologises to SA Ndabeni-Abrahams says that public servants must stop doing business with the state. She held several meetings to highlight this. In a statement, the minister says the move will help protect the integrity of her office.